OL,3,CMum lives in 'excruciating pain' after
OL,4,CKetamine destroys her bladder
OL,6,FA young mother who spent years
OL,7,Faddicted to ketamine is urging others
OL,8,Fto seek help before it is too late -
OL,9,Fafter her usage caused irreversible
OL,10,Fdamage to her bladder.
OL,12,FAmber Currah, 27, began using the
OL,13,Fpowerful drug known widely as a horse
OL,14,Ftranquilliser when she was 17-years-
OL,15,Fold, unaware of the long-term risks.
OL,17,FBut what started as casual use at
OL,18,Fsocial gatherings for the mum, from
OL,19,FMorecambe, quickly escalated into
OL,20,Faddiction.
