OL,3,CMum lives in 'excruciating pain' after
OL,4,CKetamine destroys her bladder
OL,6,FShe says ketamine initially "calmed
OL,7,Fher mind", but she soon became
OL,8,Fdependent, even as she started to
OL,9,Fnotice painful signs her health was
OL,10,Fdeteriorating.
OL,12,F"I realised bladder damage was
OL,13,Fstarting, but the only thing that
OL,14,Fwould take away the pain was to keep
OL,15,Ftaking ketamine," she said.
OL,17,FNow, Amber lives with excruciating
OL,18,Fpain, constant burning sensations and
OL,19,Fincontinence, and doctors have warned
OL,20,Fshe may eventually require a bladder
OL,21,Ftransplant due to extensive scarring.
